{
  "stem": "25831.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's why I can understand that my parents were very reluctant to make certain preparations to leave.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncle who was a radiologist, Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Cohen, was married to my mother's sister, decided to leave Germany in 1934 because his daughter had joined after the Nazis came to power the German socialist students union.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after she did that, the Gestapo came to their house and did a house search to find out whether they had subversive material.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that house search scared them so, the parents, that they decided they better leave as soon as possible.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And at that time my uncle received an invitation from Mount Sinai Hospital in Chicago, which had only a visiting sort of radiology department.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That means they didn't have a full-time radiologist.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Offered him a job to become the head of a new radiology department at Mount Sinai.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my uncle grabbed this opportunity.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he came here and he accepted it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he started that x-ray department.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he brought some wonderful refugees with him to assist him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He had only one arm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He had lost one arm in World War I.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He had been a surgeon before and switched to radiology, roentgenology, because he couldn't operate anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He brought some wonderful roentgenologists with him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "One was a Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Denelius ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the other one was a Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Ahrendt, A-H-R-E-N-D-T, who had left Germany also and became the personal physician to the Shah of Iran.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But he didn't because he accepted that position because it got him out of Germany and also because he liked to riot.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But then he didn't like it with the Shah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It wasn't his kind of Shah, quoting somebody who was Kennedy's assistant who once said that about the Shah of Iran.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
